notes: First foundry to provide 28nm GP process in 2011; expanded into comprehensive 28nm portfolio incl. 28HPC, 28HPC+, ULP and automotive-grade specialties supporting mobile, IoT and automotive applications

Derived from 28nm technology; 22ULP targets low power and cost efficiency for consumer and mobile electronics, while 22ULL further reduces leakage using ULL devices and SRAM for IoT and wearable applications
